# Containers & ECR

## Why containers

**Image** = app + runtime + deps, **runs identically anywhere**, boots in seconds, shares the host kernel. Fits where Lambda doesn't:

- **Long-running** beyond the 15-min cap
- **Sustained CPU/mem** — per-hour beats per-invocation
- Fine **runtime control** · already-containerised apps

AWS runs them 3 ways: **ECS** (native) · **EKS** (Kubernetes) · **Fargate** (serverless host, under either).

## ECR — the registry

Managed, **IAM-integrated** image registry (private Docker Hub). Per account/region + public `public.ecr.aws`.

- **Scanning** (basic on push / enhanced via Inspector)
- **Lifecycle policies**, cross-region **replication**, **KMS** at rest
- Auth = **short-lived token** (`get-login-password`)
